  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The American Academy of Paediatrics recognizes multiple benefits of breastfeeding to both the
      term and premature newborn, particularly with regard to protection from infectious agents.
      Studies have demonstrated decreased rates of bacteraemia, meningitis, respiratory and urinary
      tract infections, necrotizing enterocolitis, and otitis media among breastfed infants
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
